h tower\", \"from\": 1569, \"to\": 1584}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It dates back to the time of King Louis XIV, at the end of the 17th century, and it rings for historic events, as it did at the end of both World Wars.\", \"from\": 1586, \"to\": 1737, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1611}, {\"ngram\": \"King Louis XIV\", \"from\": 1615, \"to\": 1629}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1641}, {\"ngram\": \"the 17th century\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1661}, {\"ngram\": \"historic events\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1695}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1717}, {\"ngram\": \"both World Wars\", \"from\": 1721, \"to\": 1736}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Emmanuel was not affected by the fire in April 2019 and on special occasions continued to be operated manually as the electrical system overcame renovation.\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1894, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1738, \"end\": 1746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\", \"score\": 0.999481824064253, \"rank\": 0.0005184445801697441, \"text\": \"Emmanuel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Immanuel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the fire\", \"from\": 1767, \"to\": 1775}, {\"ngram\": \"April\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1784}, {\"ngram\": \"special occasions\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1814}, {\"ngram\": \"the electrical system\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 1873}, {\"ngram\": \"renovation\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1893}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It has rung several times since the fire, at Easter and Christmas, and for special occasions such as the death of Pope Benedict XVI,\\\" Father Ribadeau Dumas told OSV News.\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 2067, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2011, \"end\": 2028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Benedict_XVI\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5336285603193377e-44, \"text\": \"Pope Benedict XVI\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", 